<subSubSection pageId="570" pageNumber="571" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="570" pageNumber="571">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1968" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Amara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="570" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="browni">Amara browni</taxonomicName>
Lindroth, 1968: 686. Type locality: &quot;Reindeer Depot, N[orth] W[est] Terr[itories]&quot; (original citation). Holotype (♂) in CNC [# 10509]. Etymology. The specific name was proposed for Williamson James Brown [1902-1977], one of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Canada’s">Canada's</normalizedToken>
leading coleopterist of his time. Brown worked at Agriculture Canada on the systematics of several families with a special interest on scarabaeids, elaterids, and chrysomelids. He was also interested by the adventive species in Canada, the problem of sibling species, and the arctic beetles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="570" pageNumber="571" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="570" pageNumber="571">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="570" pageNumber="571">This species is known from a few localities in Yukon Territory and the Anderson River delta in northern Northwest Territories (Lindroth 1968: 687).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
